# ArLibs Project Structure

This document outlines the structure of the ArLibs Minecraft plugin library, which serves as a foundation for extending other projects.

## Main Plugin Class

The main entry point is [src/main/kotlin/dev/arteam/arlibs/ArLibs.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/dev/arteam/arlibs/ArLibs.kt), which initializes the plugin and provides access to the library's core functionality.

## Utility Packages

### Color Utilities

The [ColorUtil](mdc:src/main/kotlin/dev/arteam/arlibs/utils/ColorUtil.kt) class provides methods for handling Minecraft text colors with support for:
- Standard color codes (`&a`, `§b`)
- Hex colors (`&#FFFFFF`, `&{#FFFFFF}`)
- Gradient colors (`<g:#FFFFFF:#000000>`)
- Rainbow colors (`<r:0.4>`)

### Logging Utilities

The [Logger](mdc:src/main/kotlin/dev/arteam/arlibs/utils/Logger.kt) class offers an enhanced logging system that:
- Supports colored output
- Ensures proper plugin attribution
- Provides debug mode capabilities

## Configuration

The plugin is configured using [build.gradle.kts](mdc:build.gradle.kts) for dependency management and build settings.

The [plugin.yml](mdc:src/main/resources/plugin.yml) file contains metadata about the plugin for Bukkit/Spigot/Paper servers.

## Project Structure

```
ArLibs/
├── src/
│   └── main/
│       ├── kotlin/
│       │   └── dev/
│       │       └── arteam/
│       │           └── arlibs/
│       │               ├── ArLibs.kt             # Main plugin class
│       │               ├── api/                  # Public API interfaces
│       │               ├── utils/                # Utility classes
│       │               │   ├── ColorUtil.kt      # Color handling
│       │               │   └── Logger.kt         # Enhanced logging
│       │               ├── config/               # Configuration handling
│       │               └── events/               # Event handling
│       └── resources/
│           ├── plugin.yml                        # Plugin metadata
│           └── config.yml                        # Default configuration
└── build.gradle.kts                              # Build configuration
```

